<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
When the work has six or more authors, cite only the name of the first author followed by et al. and 
the date. (Note the full stop after et al.).
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith et al. (2056) found that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: A recent study (Smith et al., 2056) found that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
When the work is referred to more than once in the same paragraph do not include the date in 
subsequent references, as long as the work cannot be confused with others cited.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	In a recent study, Smith et al. (2056) showed that&hellip; Smith et al. also found 
	that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation, use quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith et al. (2056) observe that &#34;we have an irreversible dependency upon digital technology&#34; 
	(p. 21).
	<br>
	Alternatively: Subsequently, &#34;we have an irreversible dependency upon digital technology&#34; 
	(Smith et al., 2056, p. 21).
</blockquote>
